<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> General </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia Denounces NATO Use of Force Against Bosnian Serbs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia Denounces NATO Use of Force Against Bosnian Serbs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1404032194 Beijing XINHUA in English 0304 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1404032194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, April 13 (XINHUA) -- The Russian State Duma 
(lower house of parliament) today condemned NATO's unilateral 
use of force against Bosnian Serbs. 
  The State Duma in a statement called for an immediate 
meeting 
of the UN Security Council to discuss NATO's military 
involvement in the Bosnian war. 
  The statement also suggested that measures be taken to 
prevent the escalation of the Bosnian conflict. 
  The UN peacekeeping force should not be used by any bloc to 
carry out military actions, the statement stressed, adding that 
Russia was worried by the fact that NATO continued its policy of 
using force as the means to solve the crisis in former 
Yugoslavia. 
  Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Sergey Lavrov also described 
as "unreasonable" NATO's air strikes against Bosnian Serb 
positions around the embattled Gorazde, saying they could only 
result in the worsening of the situation there. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

