<H3> <TI>   Clinton Condemns Attack in Hadera, Israel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Clinton Condemns Attack in Hadera, Israel </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1404050094 Beijing XINHUA in English 0453 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1404050094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Washington, April 13 (XINHUA) -- U.S. President Bill 
Clinton today issued a statement condemning a new attack in 
Hadera, Israel. 
  A bus in Hadera was bombed earlier today with six Israelis 
killed and 28 wounded, including 18 Israeli soldiers. 
  "This action, like those before it, is a further attempt by 
extremists to derail the peace process," Clinton said, adding 
that "they must not be allowed to succeed." 
  "We believe the best response to the enemies of peace is to 
demonstrate that negotiations can change realities on the ground 
and give hope to Israelis and Palestinians for a peaceful 
future," Clinton said. 
  White House Press Secretary Dee Dee Myers said that Clinton 
telephoned Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin to express 
condolences over today's bus explosion. 
  Clinton stressed the urgency of bringing an end to the 
on-going talks on implementing the PLO-Israeli peace accord 
signed in Washington on September 13 1993. 
  During the telephone talk, Rabin agreed with Clinton on the 
need to reach prompt agreement on the implementation, Myers said. 

</TEXT>

