<F P=102>   OW1304104694 Beijing XINHUA in English 1023 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1304104694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 13 (XINHUA) -- Vice-Chairman of the 
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress Wu Jieping 
extended profound condolences to the embassies of Burundi and 
Rwanda over the death of their heads of state. 
  Wu offered solicitude this afternoon for the death of 
President Juvenal Habyarimana and Prime Minister Uwilingiyimana 
Agathe of Rwanda and President Cyprian Ntayaminas of Burundi. 
  Chinese President Jiang Zemin and Premier Li Peng sent 
wreaths to the embassies. 
