<H3> <TI>   German Chancellor Kohl Meets Shanghai Mayor </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    German Chancellor Kohl Meets Shanghai Mayor </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1404030094 Beijing XINHUA in English 0214 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1404030094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn, April 13 (XINHUA) -- German Chancellor Helmut 
Kohl expressed his satisfaction at the Sino-German economic 
cooperation while meeting with a visiting Chinese mayor here 
today. 
  He also expressed his confidence that China's present 
economic policy will succeed. 
  Kohl asked Huang Ju, mayor of China's biggest city of 
Shanghai, to convey his greetings to Chinese leaders. 
  Huang, who arrived in Germany on Sunday for an eight-day 
visit, told Kohl that Shanghai plans to set up an international 
group corporation in Europe with its headquarters in Hamburg. 

</TEXT>

