<H3> <TI>   Youth Research Society Inaugurated in Beijing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Youth Research Society Inaugurated in Beijing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1304140794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1326 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1304140794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 13 (XINHUA) -- The China Youth 
Research Society, the country's first mass academic organization 
for the study of youth, was inaugurated here today. 
  Experts noted that this marks a new stage of the research on 
youth in China. 
  Zhao Shi, member of the secretariat of the Communist Youth 
League of China (CYLC), was elected president of the society. 
  The society already has 239 members, who come from the CYLC, 
higher education institutions, from the social sciences and from 
enterprises. It will concentrate on the study of new trends and 
new problems involving modern young people and will make 
constructive proposals with social and theoretical value. 
  Lei Jieqiong, vice-chairwoman of the Standing Committee of 
the current (Eighth) National People's Congress, attended the 
inauguration ceremony today. 
  Zhao Zongnai, executive deputy head of the Organization 
Department of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of 
China, expressed congratulations on the inauguration of the 
society, on behalf of all the advisors of the new organisation. 

</TEXT>

