<H3> <TI>   Coastal Defense Boats To Standardize Names, Numbers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Coastal Defense Boats To Standardize Names, Numbers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1304050494 Beijing Central Television Program One Network 
in Mandarin 1400 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1304050494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing Central Television Program One Network 
in Mandarin 1400 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=105> Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Video report by unidentified correspondent; from the "Night </F>
News" program] 
  [Text] From a national meeting on coastal defense 
management that closed in Hangzhou on 16 March, this reporter 
learned the Ministry of Public Security has decided, beginning 1 
April, to organize into a single unit all public security 
coastal defense boats assigned to ensure offshore security and 
crack down on smuggling. These boats will use standardized 
names and serial numbers. When performing antismuggling and 
coastal patrol tasks, boats should bring with them proof issued 
by the Ministry of Public Security and which cannot be 
counterfeited that they are allowed to perform offshore duties; 
personnel performing offshore duty should wear a standardized 
duty-performing badge. Domestic and foreign ships may refuse 
inspection by patrol boats and personnel that do not meet the 
aforementioned requirements. [video shows marine policemen in 
action, an offshore duty-performing authorization booklet, and a 
duty-performing badge on a marine policeman's arm] 

</TEXT>

