<H3> <TI>   Air Force Test-Flight Regiment Receives Commendation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Air Force Test-Flight Regiment Receives Commendation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1304051294 Beijing Central Television Program One Network 
in Mandarin 1400 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1304051294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing Central Television Program One Network 
in Mandarin 1400 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=105> Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video; from the "Night News" </F>
program] 
  [Text] [Video opens with a medium-range shot of test 
pilots, then cuts to show a pilot entering an aircraft to 
prepare for flight. Video also shows aircraft taking off, 
dropping bombs, and firing missiles, as well as computer rooms 
which monitor test flights] An Air Force test-flight 
regiment--China's only regiment which can fly every Chinese-made 
fighter, bomber, and transport--was recently commended by the 
Air Force and received a Second Class Merit Citation. 
  Over the past two decades, the regiment has made test 
flights 
and issued certificates of inspection for 43 new kinds of 
Chinese-built aircraft, have completed some 880 major scientific 
research projects, and have filled in the gaps in nearly 10 
aviation projects. Wang Ang, (Hua Jun), (Wang Guanyang), Huang 
Bingxin, and other model heroes have emerged. The regiment has 
prevented over 10,000 disasters encountered in some 60,000 
scientific research flights, has saved hundreds of million yuan 
for the state, and has created miracles in the world history of 
test flights. 

