<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   First Phase of Shenzhen Yantian Port Completed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    First Phase of Shenzhen Yantian Port Completed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1404110894 Beijing XINHUA in English 1050 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1404110894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shenzhen, April 14 (XINHUA) -- The first 
construction phase of Shenzhen Yantian port was completed today. 
  As the only deep-water port in south China, the planned 
facilities will consist of 50 berths, each of which has a 
capacity to accommodate ships exceeding 10,000 tons. 
  Sources said that when the berths go into operation, the 
annual handling capacity will reach eight million standard 
containers. 
  The first-phase construction of Yantian port consisted of 58 
projects, including a 24-kilometer highway from the port to 
Pinghu Railway Station, a 72-kilometer highway from the port to 
Huizhou city, six berths with an annual handling capacity of 2.8 
million tons and a container yard with an area of 240,000 square 
meters, and a 6.29-square-kilometer infrastructural base for 
water- and electricity-supply and telecommunications services. 
  The port is designed to be computer-controlled and it now 
has 
hundreds of up-to-date port machines. 
  The second phase of the construction of the port will start 
later this year. 

</TEXT>

