<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   City in Jiangxi Improves Transport Infrastructure </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    City in Jiangxi Improves Transport Infrastructure </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1304120694 Beijing XINHUA in English 0953 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1304120694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nanchang, April 13 (XINHUA) -- Jiujiang City in 
east China's Jiangxi Province has improved its transportation 
and telecommunications conditions in the past two years. 
  Situated on the Chang Jiang River, Jiujiang was designated 
an 
open city by the central government in May 1992. 
  Since then, Jiujiang has been working hard to improve its 
environment in a bid to draw foreign investment. 
  The transportation situation has been greatly improved as 
the 
Chang Jiang River Bridge at Jiujiang and the Nanchang-Jiujiang 
Highway were opened to traffic a year ago. 
  The construction of a highway linking Jiujiang and 
Jingdezhen, the "capital of porcelain", is about to start. 
  The Port of Jiujiang is also open to all foreign vessels. 
Routes for container ships from Jiujiang to other parts of the 
world have also been opened. 
  The city is to open air routes to Shanghai, Xiamen, 
Guangzhou, Shenzhen and Haikou before long, in addition to the 
established destinations of Beijing, Nanjing and Huiyang. 
  Three railways including the Beijing-Kowloon line under 
construction now converge at Jiujiang. 
  Communications construction has also been accelerated. By 
the end of last year, all telephones in the city were automated, 
linking Jiujiang with 1,600 cities and towns in China and more 
than 180 countries and regions. 
  The improved environment has attracted a growing number of 
foreign investors. Jiujiang absorbed 30.64 million U.S. dollars 
investment in some 30 industries last year. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

