<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Spokesman Holds News Briefing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Spokesman Holds News Briefing </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Announces NPC Delegation Visit </H4>

<F P=102> OW1404083494 Beijing XINHUA in English 0808 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1404083494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 14 (XINHUA) -- A delegation from 
China's National People's Congress (NPC) is to visit New 
Zealand, Western Samoa, Papua New Guinea and Australia later 
this month, a Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman announced here 
this afternoon. 
  According to the spokesman, the delegation, which will be 
headed by Vice-Chairman Tian Jiyun of the NPC Standing 
Committee, will pay official good-will visits to the above 
mentioned four countries from April 18 at the invitation of 
their parliaments. 

</TEXT>

