<F P=100> East Europe </F>
<H3> <TI>   Qiao Shi Receives Albanian Counterpart </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Qiao Shi Receives Albanian Counterpart </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1204174794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1431 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1204174794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 12 (XINHUA) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of 
the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC), 
China's parliament, met with Pjeter Arbnori, president of the 
Albanian people's parliament, here this afternoon. 
  Noting that contacts between the two countries have been on 
the rise over the past few years, Qiao expressed the conviction 
that Arbnori's China visit will promote the further development 
of bilateral ties. 
  "We are willing to develop friendly ties with all other 
countries, based on the principles of peaceful co-existence," 
Qiao said. 
  Arbnori said that China was and is a great nation which has 
made special contributions to the progress of mankind. 
  Albania appreciates what China has achieved in the past few 
years, Arbnori told his host. 
  Qiao said that China is still in the process of development, 
with coastal areas developing faster. He added that it will 
take great efforts of generations to bring about a fairly high 
level of development in the country's central and western part. 
  During the meeting, Qiao expressed appreciation of Albania's 
stance of "one China" and not developing official ties with 
Taiwan. 
  After the meeting, Qiao hosted a banquet in Arbnori's honor. 
  Also in the afternoon, NPC Vice-Chairperson Lei Jieqiong 
held 
talks with the Albanian delegation. 
  Arbnori and his party arrived here earlier today as guests 
of 
the NPC standing committee. Apart from Beijing, they are 
scheduled to visit Shenzhen in southern China. 

</TEXT>

