<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Hong Kong </F>
<H3> <TI>   UK, Chinese Officials Discuss Hong Kong Issues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UK, Chinese Officials Discuss Hong Kong Issues </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1204161594 Beijing XINHUA in English 1546 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1204161594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hong Kong, April 12 (XINHUA) -- Experts from both 
sides of the Sino-British Joint Liaison Group (JLG) met here 
today to discuss issues concerning the Hong Kong residents after 
1997. 
  Chen Zuoer, resident representative of the Chinese team of 
the group, said that experts from both sides exchanged views on 
matters such as right of abode, visa abolition, and the Hong 
Kong Special Administrative Region travel documents. 
  He said that the Chinese side attaches great importance to 
the above issues as they constitute the major contents of the 
transfer of power in 1997, adding that he hoped a legitimate and 
reasonable solution towards the issues could be worked out 
between the two sides. 

</TEXT>

