  In 1993, total amount of post and telecommunications 
business 
in the whole province reached 540 million yuan, an increase of 
95.3 percent over the previous year. Post and 
telecommunications facilities were greatly improved, and 
communication capacity was enormously strengthened. By the end 
of 1993, Hainan Province had a total of 4,909 trunk telephone 
all lines, 109 cable lines, 211,000 city telephones, 10,400 
mobile telephone subscribers, and 136,300 wireless paging 
subscribers. The rate of popularization of city telephones in 
the province was 12.6 percent, exceeding the national average 
level, among which that of the Haikou rose from 16.6 percent the 
previous year to 27.9 percent, jumping up to first place among 
China's provincial capitals. 
  V. Domestic Trade and Market Prices 
  Consumption demand was brisk, which gave rise to price 
rises, 
and commodity retail sales grew by a big margin. In 1993 the 
amount of social commodity retail sales in the whole province 
totalled 7.736 billion yuan, an increase of 32.6 percent over 
the previous year, and retail sales of consumer goods amounted 
to 7.373 billion yuan, an increase of 34.0 percent over the 
previous year (with the factor of price rises deducted, the 
actual growth was 8.2 percent). Retail sales of the 
agricultural means of production totalled 364 million yuan, an 
increase of 9.7 percent over that of the previous year. Business 
volume of urban and rural fair trade amounted to 3.657 billion 
yuan, an increase of 55.5 percent over the previous year. 
  The urban retail sales volume amounted to 5.911 billion 
yuan, 
an increase of 42.7 percent over the previous year, and rural 
retail sales amounted to 1.826 billion yuan, up by 8.0 percent. 
The retail sales volume of various economic types was as 
follows: 


